"{\"uid\": \"houston.culturemap.com-news-sports-gymnastics-olympic-trials-2024-biles\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The road to Paris  The 2024 Summer Olympics Opening Ceremony is just a month away, so it'sfinallytime to pick the high-profile gymnastics teams who will represent the United Statesin Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12, \"end\": 17, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.258245926593111e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many powerhouse Texan athletes - including several who train in Houston - are among the leading contenders.\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"score\": 0.999839526317117, \"rank\": 0.0001604970877510137, \"text\": \"Houston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The path to Paris ran through Fort Worth recently at theXfinity U.S.\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.258245926593111e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 0.9999999997667146, \"rank\": 2.317124570012346e-10, \"text\": \"Fort Worth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics Championships, where the top finishers earned their invitations toU.S.\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.8233924821738834, \"rank\": 0.21448764426634462, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic Team Trials.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This weekend (June 27-30), they will go flip-to-flip and vault-to-vault in Minneapolis; who will stick the landing and get a chance to compete for Olympic glory?\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.87198936942326e-17, \"text\": \"Minneapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans will not know until Sunday night when the full team is announced.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(See schedule, below.)\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition will be fierce.\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sixteen women and 20 men will vie for just five spots each, plus two traveling and two non-traveling replacement athletes for each squad.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And realistically, the women are competing for three or four spots; barring any catastrophes, Houston's own all-time greatSimone Bileswill lead the team.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 1054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"score\": 0.999839526317117, \"rank\": 0.0001604970877510137, \"text\": \"Houston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Houston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also expected to make the cut:Shilese Jones, six-time World medalist.\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1085, \"end\": 1098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shilese Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After that, the field is open ... and deep.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jordan Chiles, Biles' training mate at World Champions Centre in Spring (which has five athletes competing), is gunning for her second Olympics.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was part of the 2020 Tokyo team thattook homethe silver medal.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.564976102036068e-17, \"text\": \"2020 Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her more modern artistry, including a Beyonce-inspired floor routine, sets her apart, but consistency is her superpower.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1503, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Will it be enough this time?\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the top contenders to help round out the team is Dallas nativeSkye Blakely.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\", \"score\": 0.9999993799039761, \"rank\": 3.533348001567647e-07, \"text\": \"Dallas\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 19-year-old, who lives in Frisco and trains atchampion-producingWOGA Gymnastics, is a two-time World team champion.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1647, \"end\": 1653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frisco_RoughRiders\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.3869402823315385e-12, \"text\": \"Frisco\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frisco_RoughRiders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frisco_RoughRiders\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was crowned the 2024 U.S. all-around silver medalist in Fort Worth, where her debut of a difficult \\\"Cheng\\\" vault put her prominently in the conversation for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1797, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 0.9999999997667146, \"rank\": 2.317124570012346e-10, \"text\": \"Fort Worth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years after her bid to make the 2020 Olympic teamended with an injury, Blakely is peaking at the right time.\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"UPDATE 6-27-2024:Skye Blakelywas injuredduring a practice at Olympic Trials on Wednesday, June 26.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daisy_Johnson\", \"score\": 0.9772814267097428, \"rank\": 0.02323884985670705, \"text\": \"Skye\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daisy_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daisy_Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday morning, USA Gymnastics announced that she will have to withdraw from competition.\", \"from\": 2